From: Arif (siot-dev-m5) <arif@southerniot.com>
Date: Fri, 01 May 2026 13:17:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix USB_IAD_DESC_SIZE: 9 -> 8 per USB 2.0 ECN

The USB Interface Association Descriptor (IAD), defined in the USB 2.0
ECN "Interface Association Descriptors" (May 2003), is exactly 8 bytes:

  bLength            (1) +
  bDescriptorType    (1) +
  bFirstInterface    (1) +
  bInterfaceCount    (1) +
  bFunctionClass     (1) +
  bFunctionSubClass  (1) +
  bFunctionProtocol  (1) +
  iFunction          (1) = 8 bytes

ESP-IDF v5.5.x release branch defines this as 9, which is incorrect and
makes the static_assert on `sizeof(usb_iad_desc_t) == USB_IAD_DESC_SIZE`
silently bake the wrong size into any code that uses the IAD type for
composite-device descriptor assembly.

ESP-IDF master has refactored USB types and the `USB_IAD_DESC_SIZE`
constant no longer exists in this form there, so the bug is implicitly
fixed in master. v5.5.x release branch retains the wrong value.

This patch corrects v5.5.4 to match the spec.

Attribution: local origin. No upstream PR exists at time of vendoring
(2026-05-01). Filing one against `release/v5.5` is logged as a deferred
task in docs/RUNBOOK.md / ADR-001 appendix.

Project: rnd-southerniot/rak3112-rs485-node (firmware repo)
Phase:   2, EC-1, 2026-05-01

Reference: USB 2.0 ECN, "Interface Association Descriptors" (May 2003)
---
 components/usb/include/usb/usb_types_ch9.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/components/usb/include/usb/usb_types_ch9.h b/components/usb/include/usb/usb_types_ch9.h
index 500a5dc5..fca00948 100644
--- a/components/usb/include/usb/usb_types_ch9.h
+++ b/components/usb/include/usb/usb_types_ch9.h
@@ -384,7 +384,7 @@ ESP_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(usb_config_desc_t) == USB_CONFIG_DESC_SIZE, "Size of us
 /**
  * @brief Size of a USB interface association descriptor in bytes
  */
-#define USB_IAD_DESC_SIZE    9
+#define USB_IAD_DESC_SIZE    8

 /**
  * @brief Structure representing a USB interface association descriptor
--
